<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph base="SL33603" principles="yes" id="IAS41_10"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>10</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 41"/><data name="paranum" value="10"/></prolog><body outputclass="bold"><p id="IAS41_P0157">An entity shall recognise a biological asset or agricultural produce when, and only when: </p><ol outputclass="static" base="SL143249" type="lower-alpha" id="IAS41_L0010"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="SL143251" id="IAS41_P0158">the entity controls                      the asset as a result of past events;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="SL143253" id="IAS41_P0159">it is probable that future economic benefits                      associated with the asset will flow to the entity; and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value>         <p base="SL143255" id="IAS41_P0160">the fair value or cost of the asset can be measured reliably.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>